      "writtenOn": "2026-05-19T18:04:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 42: 🟡 Minor thread-safety note: `bufferWidth` and `bufferHeight` are read from the UI thread in `configureTransform` but written from the camera thread in `setBufferSize`. Since both are plain `Int` fields (not volatile or atomic), there\u0027s a theoretical visibility issue. In practice this is likely fine on Android (UI thread will see the update on next layout pass), but marking them `@Volatile` or using an `AtomicInteger` would be more correct.",
      "revId": "f3f4b04fdd9cc65d5b25402d7460ce856625bcfb",
